[3] UK (Tyne side]
Date: Wed 13 Feb 2013
Source: Jarrow and Hebburn Gazette [edited]
http://www.jarrowandhebburngazette.com/news/health/warning-as-measles-cases-increase-1-5402234


Warning as measles cases increase
-----------------------------
Parents in South Tyneside are being urged to vaccinate their children as cases of measles continue to rise. The Health Protection Agency (HPA) says that since September [2012], 82 confirmed cases and 73 suspected cases of the illness have been reported. These include 19 confirmed and 10 suspected cases in the past week.

HPA immunisation lead Julia Waller said: "There is no treatment for measles but it can be prevented by the MMR vaccine, and 2 doses are required to ensure the best protection." That's why we're urging parents to make sure that their children are fully immunised and have had 2 doses of the jab. "In fact, anyone who is unsure about their own immunisation status should do the same."

